Store is a simple class which can be initialized with a name and initial
value. It has two methods: dump, which stringifies the data, and dump
which converts it back to a data structure.

Each time we run a mutating function on our Riot component, we update
the store. When the page is reloaded, we initialize the store and if it
is defined use it for the initial issues.

TIL: the `->` macro in clojure DOES take partial functions, but they
need to be in extra brackets:

```
> (defn foo [a b] (+a b))
> (-> 2 (partial 1)) ;; returns the function
> (-> 2 ((partial 1)));; returns 3
```
